dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha st Ronchi b Sodhi 42 (44b 6x4 0x6 81m) SR: 95.45

dismissalComment.html: legspinner's dream ball, absolutely terrific, tosses it up on middle and induces Chibhabha to come out of his crease as he tries to work it through the leg side, it spins away from him exaggeratively and beats the outside edge. Chibhabha is well outside his crease and Ronchi doesn't have much to do but does it well. Awesome delivery

dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams run out (Guptill) 26 (45b 0x4 0x6 64m) SR: 57.77

dismissalComment.html: what's happened there?! Outstanding fielding from Martin Guptill. Raza had gone on the back foot to push a ball towards mid-on, and Williams set off for a run from the non-striker's end. Guptill came sprinting in from midwicket to dive full length and cut off the shot. Seeing that, Raza sent Williams back ... Guptill was still flat on the ground on his stomach when he back-handed the ball along the ground and hit the stumps direct to run Williams out by miles

dismissalText.commentary: Martin Guptill not out 116 (138b 11x4 1x6 169m) SR: 84.05
Tom Latham not out 110 (116b 7x4 2x6 169m) SR: 94.82

headshotImage.caption: Ish Sodhi player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ish Sodhi player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: flat and quick down leg, Latham tries to sweep but no one can get to that. It beats the keeper as well and runs away to the boundary for five extras which is good enough for NZ to level the series.

commentPostTextItems.html: 4.15pm So that brings to an end a good win for NZ. There is all to play for in the series decider on Friday, so join us then. Until then, ciao.

4.05pm So, a thoroughly convincing win for NZ, they take it with 10 wickets left. Cannot get any more convincing that that. A massive partnership from Guptill and Latham. I cannot recollect too many chances being given to Zimbabwe, great shot selection. The second consecutive game being decided via a wide in this series. Zimbabwe's bowling lacked penetration even with plenty of turn in the wicket. They did not create any half-chances even, never mind chances.

Chigumbura: "We are disappointed. We lost too many wickets up front, Williams and Raza brought it back for us. But 236 wasn't good enough. I thought it was a good wicket to bat on. If we get the chance, we need to make sure we are ruthless."

Williamson: Much-improved effort. The tone was set early on with the ball, the fielding effort was much better and we pride ourselves on that, which wasn't there last game. We need to play our best cricket again on Friday. You want to improve all the time, which is great for learning too.
Martin Guptill and Tom Latham will share the Man of the Match
Guptill: "It is tough early on actually, but when you brush that off, it is easier to bat on. Happy for Latham."
Latham: "Happy to get the monkey off the back. Struggled a bit at the start but when we got through that, we knocked it off in 10-run blocks."

David: "Kiwis on track to break the record: Highest run chase without losing a wicket. Previous bests: Sri Lanka 230 (ODI 3145) Pakistan 226 (ODI 3190) and West Indies 221 (ODI 717). An achievement worthy of recognition" Indeed..

commentTextItems.html: short on middle and leg, Latham pulls off the front foot towards square leg
flat, quick and wide. Latham is beaten on the cut
tossed up again on middle, Guptill drives with soft hands towards long-off, halfway through the first run they realise there is an east two on offer and they make it easily too.
opens the face of the bat to deflect the full delivery wide off point

commentPreTextItems.html: sathish2888: "This is a perfect response from World Cup Finalists.."

commentTextItems.html: slow turn once more, drifts on his pads and Latham turns it to short fine leg
slow turn once more, Guptill jumps back and turns it to midwicket against the spin
follows it with a bit of caution, defends the fuller delivery off the front foot
huge six! Absolutely massive. A slow, flighted googly and Guptill picks it. That is all he needed, put one foot forward and slogs it over long-on for a humongous six
this time he gets the gap, a bit wider, Guptill rocks back and cuts it to the sweeper cover
slightly wider outside off and Guptill stays back and cuts to point
slower on middle, pushed back to the bowler
skids on with the arm from a fuller length, Guptill gets back and punches back to the bowler
fuller and flatter, Guptill blocks on the front foot

commentPreTextItems.html: Williams to bowl from around the wicket

commentTextItems.html: a bit short first up on middle and leg, pulled well off the front foot to square leg
well bowled, he is still tossing it up to his credit, but it is too short and Guptill can get back and cut to point
a bit short and Latham rocks back again, punched down to long-on
connects with the sweep this time, good connection too, it is too slow to cause much trouble. Latham gets down on a knee and lofts the sweep over fine leg
pitched outside off and spins back in, Latham rocks back and plays it late but hits it to the bowler
clears one leg and drives it with the spin to cover
